Package: the420coind
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - daemon
 The420Coin is an experimental new digital currency that enables anonymous, instant
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. The420Coin uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. The420Coin Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides the daemon, the420coind, and the CLI tool
 the420coin-cli to interact with the daemon.

Package: the420coin-qt
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - Qt GUI
 The420Coin is an experimental new digital currency that enables anonymous, instant
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. The420Coin uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. The420Coin Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides The420Coin-Qt, a GUI for The420Coin based on Qt.

Package: the420coin-tx
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer digital currency - standalone transaction tool
 The420Coin is an experimental new digital currency that enables anonymous, instant
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. The420Coin uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. The420Coin Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides the420coin-tx, a command-line transaction creation
 tool which can be used without a the420coin daemon.  Some means of
 exchanging minimal transaction data with peers is still required.
